<refentry id="bif.ReadText" xreflabel="ReadText">

<refmeta>
<indexterm>
<primary>ReadText</primary>
</indexterm>

<refentrytitle>ReadText</refentrytitle>
<refmiscinfo>Built-in function</refmiscinfo>
</refmeta>

<refnamediv>
<refname>ReadText</refname>
<refpurpose>
Reads data from an input stream as text
</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv>
<synopsis>
ReadText[input<->INPUT, {x<->}, until->TEXT] =: INPUT
ReadText[input<->INPUT, {x<->}, n->INTEGER] =: INPUT
</synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsect1><title>Description</title>
<para>
<function>ReadText</function> 
reads data of type <type>TEXT</type> from the input stream and assigns it to
<parameter>x</parameter>.  The first signature reads from <parameter>input</parameter> until the
string <parameter>until</parameter> is reached.  For example, setting
<parameter>until</parameter><literal>-&gt;"\n"</literal>
will read a line of text from <parameter>input</parameter>.  The
second signature reads <parameter>n</parameter> characters from 
<parameter>input</parameter>.  
</para>
</refsect1>

